cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper is about comparing different methods of feature importance in text classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning models, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) and computer vision (CV) to some extent, so cs.IR and cs.CV are also possible sub-categories.
